definitions: A person who decorates something with a sprig or sprigs; especially a person (typically a woman) employed to embroider or embellish fabric, garments, etc., with designs or motifs resembling sprigs of foliage, flowers, etc. Now chiefly historical.

etymologies: mid 19th century (in an earlier sense). Partly from sprig + -er

definitions: (chiefly Australian Rules Football). A person who is responsible for studding or maintaining the boots of a team, etc.
